(power_internal, power_logic).explanation: Power logic is a fundamental component that contributes to the total internal power consumption of a processor;

(power_internal, area_cell_area).explanation: Cell area is a physical design metric that doesn't directly cause or result from internal power consumption, though they may be influenced by common design decisions;

(power_internal, power_register).explanation: Register power consumption is a component that contributes to the overall internal power consumption of the processor;
